The engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, adding to the supportive atmosphere of the event. Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. Groups of friends mark target employers on the event map, and an alumni panel discusses how to prepare for technical interviews. Additionally, alumni volunteers share quick pep talks near the coffee station. Meanwhile, tech companies display demo screens showing their latest apps.

Camera crews from the university media team capture interviews, while event staff are positioned at the entrance to scan registrations and distribute lanyards to attendees. Representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths, and volunteers actively engage in cleanup efforts, stacking collapsed booths and gathering leftover brochures. Students compare swag items like water bottles and phone chargers, and groups of friends mark target employers on the event map. The dean stops by to thank recruiters for supporting the university. Near the exit, a post-event survey link flashes on the monitors.

Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures as groups of friends mark target employers on the event map, and announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair.
